    "/pix2fa": {
      "post": {
        "summary": "Pix2FA",
        "deprecated": false,
        "description": "Pix2FA is a security feature designed to protect users from scams and fraud—particularly *“man-in-the-middle”* attacks.\nThis verification step applies **only to new users** or if explicitly required by the partner.\n\n### **How It Works**\n#### **First Payment**\nAfter the end user successfully makes its first deposit, Eulen will lock the deposit and send a payment R$ 0,01 (one BRL cent) to the user's bank account (the same used for the deposit).\n\n#### **Verification Code**\nThis R$ 0,01 payment will include a 6-digit verification code in the payment description. The end user must provide this code to the Eulen Partner through the partner’s usual interface.\n\n#### **Partner Validation**\nIn order to unlock the deposit, the Eulen Partner must submit the provided Pix2FA code to Eulen via:\n- the `pix2fa` endpoint, or\n- the `/pix2fa` telegram bot command.\n\nOnce the code is correct and validated by Eulen, the deposit will be unlocked and the DePix will be sent.\n\n#### **Checking Pending Verifications**\nPartners can identify deposits awaiting Pix2FA verification by querying deposits with the `pending_pix2fa` status through the:\n- `deposit-status` endpoint, or\n- `deposits` endpoint.",
        "tags": [
          "API Endpoints"
        ],
        "parameters": [
          {
            "name": "X-Nonce",
            "in": "header",
            "description": "A random uuid string to identify an CLIENT INTENTION as unique. In case of retrying the same request, always use the same nonce. For new operations, use a new one. By default, if this param is empty, a new nonce would be generated.",
            "required": false,
            "format": "uuid",
            "type": "string",
            "x-example": ""
          },
          {
            "name": "X-Async",
            "in": "header",
            "description": "Can be true, false or auto. If not auto forces API async or sync behavior.",
            "default": "auto",
            "type": "string",
            "x-example": "auto"
          },
          {
            "name": "body",
            "in": "body",
            "schema": {
              "type": "object",
              "properties": {
                "pixTwoFactorCode": {
                  "type": "string",
                  "description": "The 6-digit pix2fa code"
                },
                "qrId": {
                  "type": "string",
                  "description": "The QR code identifier (uuid)"
                }
              },
              "required": [
                "pixTwoFactorCode",
                "qrId"
              ]
            }
          }
        ],
        "responses": {
          "200": {
            "description": "",
            "headers": {
              "X-Request-ID": {
                "example": "8ddc3426-1425-4d80-b588-a05371119da0",
                "required": true,
                "description": "UUID for each request",
                "type": "string"
